{{Quote|Ten to one it's the Frezhlix; they've been feuding with the Sif'kries ever since we chased the Empire out of the area.|Corran Horn|<ref name="Specter of the Past">''[[Specter of the Past]]''</ref>}}
The '''Frezhlix''' (sing. '''Frezh''') were a [[Species/Legends|species]] that lived in the [[Sif'kric system/Legends|Sif'kric system]]. They began feuding with the [[Sif'krie]]s soon after the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] pulled out of the [[Sector/Legends|sector]] and the [[Star system/Legends|system]] that the two species shared.

Concurrently with the [[Caamas Document]] crisis of [[19 ABY/Legends|19 ABY]], a Frezhlix fleet blockaded the Sif'krie [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] of [[Sif'kric]]. The Frezhlix justification for this was the Sif'krie's opposition to the [[Drashtine Initiative]] in their [[sector assembly]], demanding that the [[Bothan/Legends|Bothans]] pay reparations for the destruction of [[Caamas/Legends|Caamas]]. As a result, their common sectoral senator was unable to vote as the Frezhlix wished. This fleet included two [[Kruk battle-wagon]]s, five [[Lancer-class frigate/Legends|''Lancer''-class frigates]] and thirty [[Jompers pursuit ship]]s.

When the Frezhlix fleet [[Blockade of Sif'kric|fired]] on a [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] task force under Generals [[Garm Bel Iblis/Legends|Garm Bel Iblis]] and [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]], who had broken through the Frezhlix battle line under pretext of investigating [[Smuggler/Legends|smugglers]], the New Republic forces returned fire and ended the blockade.

